# _headers — Cloudflare Pages custom headers
#
# Previously had a Content-Encoding: br rule for /index.wasm — that's
# gone now that build.py splits large wasm files into .part1/.part2
# instead of brotli-compressing them (see setup/build.py, section 5
# of the README). Those parts are raw bytes, not brotli, so keeping
# `Content-Encoding: br` here would make browsers try to brotli-decode
# them and fail.
#
# Whatever goes here gets copied into export/ as-is by build.py on every
# run — this file (in game/template/) is the source of truth, don't edit
# the copy inside export/ directly.
#
# ── CROSS-ORIGIN ISOLATION OFF (Nimiq Hub popup fix) ─────────────────────────
# THE actual root cause of the persistent "Invalid Request" / "Connection was
# closed" error on the Nimiq Hub web sign-in popup. The DEPLOYED page (served
# by Cloudflare Pages, NOT the Go backend) was coming back with:
#     cross-origin-opener-policy: same-origin
#     cross-origin-embedder-policy: require-corp
# i.e. a fully cross-origin-ISOLATED page. Those two together sever the
# window.opener link on ANY cross-origin popup (hub.nimiq.com) — so inside the
# popup window.opener is null, Hub's own 1s connect-timeout handler
# (nimiq/hub RpcApi.ts branches on `window.opener === null`) abandons the
# postMessage handshake and shows its "Invalid Request" page, which our RPC
# client then surfaces as "Connection was closed". This was NOT fixable from
# the Go backend's headers: the HTML document is served by Cloudflare Pages,
# whose header layer is controlled by THIS file — the Go COOP/COEP changes
# only ever applied to /backend/* API responses, never to index.html.
#
# Setting both to their non-isolating values here explicitly OVERRIDES the
# stale/default isolation that was being served, restoring the classic
# behavior where a cross-origin popup keeps its opener — exactly what
# popup-based auth (OAuth, Google Sign-In, Nimiq Hub) needs. Safe: this
# single-threaded Godot export never needed SharedArrayBuffer/threads (see
# index.html's Engine features {threads:false} +
# GODOT_CONFIG['ensureCrossOriginIsolationHeaders']=false), so losing
# crossOriginIsolated/SAB costs nothing.
#
# ── CSP (broad/permissive on purpose) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Fixes "loads to 100%, then the page reloads itself" on some mobile
# browsers/webviews: script-src-elem and connect-src were being blocked by the
# host's default CSP (unpkg.com, wasm/pck fetches). Intentionally wide open for
# now — tighten later (swap https:/wss: wildcards for the real backend + CDN
# domains) once confirmed stable.
#
# NOTE (Cloudflare _headers format): all headers for a path must sit directly
# under the path line with NO blank line between them — a blank line ends the
# rule block. Keep COOP/COEP/CSP contiguous below.
/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: unsafe-none
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: unsafe-none
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self' https: wss: blob: data:; script-src 'self' https: blob: data: 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval' 'wasm-unsafe-eval'; script-src-elem 'self' https: blob: data: 'unsafe-inline'; worker-src 'self' https: blob: data:; connect-src 'self' https: wss: blob: data:; style-src 'self' https: 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' https: blob: data:; font-src 'self' https: data:; media-src 'self' https: blob: data:; manifest-src 'self' https:; frame-src 'self' https:; child-src 'self' https: blob:; object-src 'none'
